Old crockery, clocks and bone china are also rarely cherished or able to be kept due to a lack of room or not fitting the look of the home.

But minimal living can have its drawbacks - 47 per cent of those who had discarded an heirloom later regretted it, because they would not be able to pass it on to their children.

 

